  <description type="morphology">Plants perennial, rhizomatous and stoloniferous, usually bulbiferous; rhizomes and stolons slender. Stems erect, aerial portion 2–32 cm, subterranean portion 1–15 cm. Leaves opposite, petiolate; blade oblanceolate to rhombic or ovate, short, 2–60 × 1–20 mm. Inflorescences ebracteate. Flowers 2–10, often replaced by bulbils; sepals 2–4 mm; petals 5, white or pink, 2–4 mm; stamens 5, anther pink or lavender. Seeds 1–1.5 mm, tuberculate; elaiosome present. 2n = 22.</description>
